subsection.p:
What if they were re-written as (a_1 b_{k+1})^2 + (a_{k+1} b_1)^2 and 2(a_1 b_{k+1} \cdot a_{k+1} b_1)? I won't keep you in suspense anymore — we're going to make use of the fact that p^2 + q^2 \geq 2pq for all p, q \in \mathbb{R}
(p - q)^2 \amp \geq 0 \implies p^2 + q^2 - 2pq \amp \geq 0 \implies p^2 + q^2 \amp \geq 2pq.
.
